===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Its original form is [[𠄎]] and its origin is uncertain. Various theories exists:
* Chen Duxiu, Guo Moruo: {{liushu|p}} – sideway view of a person with protruding breasts. Original form of {{och-l|奶}}
* Zhu Fangpu: {{liushu|p}} – a rope. Original form of {{och-l|繩}}
* Wang Yunzhi, Shihong: {{liushu|p}} – a rope in midair being thrown. Used as a component in {{och-l|扔}}.
* Lin Yiguang: {{liushu|i}} – the shape of dragging or pulling.
Unrelated to [[廴]].

===Etymology 1===
; “you; your”
: From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*na-ŋ||you}}.
; "then; now"
: Related to {{cog|bo|ན|pos=postposition following temporal causes}} ({{zh-ref|Coblin, 1986}}).

